divs: sighting detailsname of photo: 'rods' in chesapeake, va location: chesapeake, va date of incident: 1\27\12, 6:44 pm description of incident: on january 27, 2012 at 6:44 pm i was taking pictures at random of a 'waxing crescent moon' as i was trying to decide what type of photo compostion i might use. the following pictures were taken as basic preliminary snap shots before focusing on closeup photos of the moon on a very clear evening. the two pictures submitted were taken within 2 seconds of each other. it wasn't until later that evening, when i was looking at the pictures, did i notice that i may have captured two 'rods' in picture dsc_8019e. i was convinced when i discovered that in the previous picture dsc_8018e had no evidence of any 'rods' what so ever. it was as if they were there one second and gone in the next. identifying the two 'rods': in picture dsc_8019e: 'rod' 1 is located almost in the center of the picture; three branches up from the fork of the tree. 'rod' 2 is much more prominent because it is in the open sky to the right of 'rod' 1. both 'rods' appear to be on the same projectory from the left to the right of the picture. equipment used: nikon d5000 (70 mm - 1\25 sec. - iso 250 - f\4.5 - shutter priority) tony surace
